cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.AI 

The paper deals with probabilistic modeling and prediction in high dimensional multivariate time-series, which is a common problem in machine learning and data science. The use of latent variables and hierarchical structures is also a common technique in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with social networks and student learning, which suggests that it may belong to cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of covariates and historical activity suggests that it may belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Retrieval) or cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing).
